Day 3: Networking Basics & Shell Scripting
Content:
Networking Commands:

Checking connectivity: ping.
Viewing network configurations: ifconfig.
Checking open ports: netstat.
Fetching content: curl.
Shell Scripting Basics:

Variables: Defining and using variables.
Loops: for, while, until.
Conditionals: if-else, case.
Tasks:
Networking Commands:

Use ping to check connectivity to a website (e.g., google.com).
Use ifconfig to view your system’s network configurations.
Use netstat -tuln to list open ports.
Fetch the content of a website using curl.
Shell Scripting Tasks:

Write a script to display "Hello, World!".
Create a script to check if a file exists and print an appropriate message.
Develop a script to list all .txt files in a directory.
Write a script to back up all .txt files to a backup directory.
Create a loop to print numbers from 1 to 10.
Write a script to check if a number is even or odd.
Develop a script to automate cleaning up temporary files in a directory.
Networking & Scripting Combined Tasks:

Write a script to ping multiple websites and log the results in a file.
Create a script to extract and display the system’s IP address.
Bonus Tasks:

Write a script to monitor system memory and CPU usage (free -m, lscpu).
Automate disk space monitoring using df -h and du.
